The paper deals with optimization algorithms for phase retrieval, which is a problem in signal processing and imaging. The use of message passing algorithms and regularization techniques suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of spectral initialization and analysis of noise sensitivity suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper suggest a possible connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
